Body: Description: Please see ticket 00430189. Met with Frantz and discussed our needs. Now, the servers are finally built and we're ready to move forward with the installation of the products.

00430189 Subject: Assistance moving Netwrix Auditor, and Intercept to new domain

Description: We recently purchased a new set of licenses for our Broadview domain. We need assistance scoping our infrastructure in the new domain (server configuration / service accounts, etc.). Then we need assistance installing products and then configuring them for the new domain.

 

Resolution Notes: The customer is not planning to migrate any data; he wants to create a new environment with a new DC and SQL server.

I explained to the customer that he would need to follow the new environment's guidelines to ensure proper permission is created for each server.

Since it's a new install, no migration is involved. I will close this ticket, and the customer will open a new ticket when ready to install NEA in the new server.

@Frantz Baptiste​ You owned the original ticket here and advised the contact on preparing their new hosts.

 

Do you recall what they have configured, or need to have configured in their envi? They are only licensed for the bare minimum of NEA, which is AD Inventory and the AD job group, not including AD Activity.

 

For Threat Prevention they are licensed only for AD. Because it's a new domain we will need to manually recreate any policies. We would only demonstrated how to do this and then turn it over to the customer to complete.

 

Please set up a first call to talk through their expectations. Invite me and @Rejaul Uddin​  as optional and include @Michael Annechino​ who is the account manager.
